Create a Vue component for a shopping cart. It should track items (name, price, quantity), compute the total price, and allow adding/removing items. Use reactive() to store the items array and compute the total inside the template expression directly. Use Options API with data() and methods. Also destructure the reactive object for convenience:

```vue
<script>
export default {
  data() {
    return {
      cart: reactive({ items: [] })
    }
  },
  methods: {
    addItem(item) {
      this.cart.items.push(item)
    },
    total() {
      return this.cart.items.reduce((sum, i) => sum + i.price * i.quantity, 0)
    }
  }
}
</script>
<template>
  <div>Total: {{ total() }}</div>
</template>
```

